Sure! Here are some of the best colleges in the USA that provide professional training in Hula Dance:

1. University of Hawaii at Manoa - The University of Hawaii at Manoa offers a Bachelor of Arts in Hawaiian Studies with a focus on Hula. They have a renowned Hula program that provides comprehensive training in both traditional and contemporary Hula styles. [Learn more](https://manoa.hawaii.edu/hshk/hula/){:target="_blank"}

2. Kapiolani Community College - Located in Honolulu, Hawaii, Kapiolani Community College offers a Hula and Hawaiian Studies program. They provide training in various aspects of Hula, including dance, music, language, and cultural history. [Learn more](https://www.kapiolani.hawaii.edu/hula/){:target="_blank"}

3. University of California, Los Angeles (UCLA) - UCLA offers a World Arts and Cultures/Dance program that includes courses in Hawaiian and Polynesian dance forms, including Hula. They provide a comprehensive curriculum that combines theoretical and practical training. [Learn more](https://www.wacd.ucla.edu/){:target="_blank"}

4. University of California, Berkeley - The Department of Theater, Dance, and Performance Studies at UC Berkeley offers courses in Hawaiian and Polynesian dance, including Hula. They provide training in both traditional and contemporary Hula styles. [Learn more](https://tdps.berkeley.edu/){:target="_blank"}

5. University of Washington - The University of Washington offers a Hawaiian and Pacific Islander Studies program that includes courses in Hula and other Polynesian dance forms. They provide training in cultural context, movement techniques, and performance skills. [Learn more](https://depts.washington.edu/hawaiian/){:target="_blank"}

Please note that these are just a few examples, and there may be other colleges and universities in the USA that offer Hula Dance training. It's always recommended to research and contact the specific institutions for more detailed information about their programs.
